W.R. Grace and Co said its EuropeanDarex division has started constuction to double capacity atits fluid cracking catalyst plant in Worms, West Germany.    The expansion is expected to cost approximately 20 mlndlrs, it said.    The expansion is in response to demand for these catalystsin Europe and the Middle East. Completion of the project isscheduled for the middle of 1988, the company said.&#3;